headline: Palo Alto Stock Leaps After Earnings. Guidance Was Upbeat.
summary: Coming into  Palo Alto  Networks’ fiscal fourth-quarter earnings report, investors may have been concerned it would continue a trend of slight disappointments in tech profits being met with punishing selloffs.  Palo Alto beat Wall Street analyst expectations in all its major metrics in the fourth quarter, as well as in its guidance for the 2026 first quarter and fiscal year.  Fourth-quarter revenue beat the consensus estimate by 1.4%, while adjusted earnings per share exceeded forecasts by 7.3%.

headline: Palo Alto Networks stock jumps on full-year outlook
summary: Palo Alto Networks (PANW) reported fiscal fourth quarter adjusted earnings of $0.95 per share. Revenue of $2.5 billion was in line with expectations. For the full year, the tech company sees adjusted earnings in a range of $3.75 to $3.85 per share, which topped the estimate of $3.69. Its full-year revenue range is $10.48 billion to $10.53 billion. The expectation was $10.44 billion. Market Domination Overtime Anchor Josh Lipton and RBC Capital Markets managing director and head of global TIMT research Matt Hedberg discuss the results. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.
